[{"Name": "11.104 Use of brand name or equal purchase descriptions.", "Content": "(a) While the use of performance specifications is preferred to encourage offerors to propose innovative solutions, the use of brand name or equal purchase descriptions may be advantageous under certain circumstances. (b) Brand name or equal purchase descriptions must include, in addition to the brand name, a general description of those salient physical, functional, or performance characteristics of the brand name item that an  equal  item must meet to be acceptable for award. Use brand name or equal descriptions when the salient characteristics are firm requirements.", "Notes":"", "Uid":"83777c6e-08d5-43bb-8183-c721819a3326"}]